main event: A civilian spotted a white, flat, long object moving from east to west at O'Hare International Airport in Chicago, Illinois on November 3, 1965.
interesting points: The object was described as being the size of a pea held at arm's length.
The object appeared to be following an aircraft and moving erratically.
The sighting lasted for approximately 30 minutes.
The witness was a civilian who called the report into the Air Force at O'Hare Airport.
No sound or trail was reported from the object.
location: Near O'Hare International Airport, Rivergrove, Illinois
